printFinalStats

private static void printFinalStats(java.util.Properties props,
                                    int opcount,
                                    int actcount,
                                    long runtime,
                                    java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> benchmarkStats,
                                    java.io.PrintWriter outpS)
                             throws java.io.IOException
Exports the measurements to either console or a file using the printer. It also loads the statistics to a file and sends them to the coordinator if BG is in rating mode.

Parameters:
opcount - The total session count.
actcount - The total action count.
runtime - The duration of the benchmark.
outpS - Used when the statistics are written on a socket for the coordinator.
props - The properties of the benchmark.
benchmarkStats - Contains the statistics of the benchmark.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - Either failed to write to output stream or failed to close it.

main

public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
